This section includes worker allowance plan information. There can be one or more allowance plan data sections per worker. 
The occurrence behavior of this section depends on how the "Include Allowance Plan Data section" integration attribute is configured. 
This section includes an "Operation" field that indicates if the section is added, removed, modified, or unchanged.
Field attributes define the behaviors and restrictions of individual fields. Enable "Include in Output" to include a field in the 
output file. Enable "Required Field" to require the field to be included in the output file. Enter a "Maximum Length" to truncate any value that exceeds the limit value.
If you specify a Payroll Interface version of 16 or later (using the "Version" integration attribute), you can define the format of date type
and date-time type fields using the "Date Format" and "Datetime Format" integration attributes.
For Boolean type fields, valid values are 0(false) and 1(true).
Fields annotated with (IA) indicate that the field value may be controlled by an integration attribute.
Fields annotated with (IM) indicate that the field value can be mapped using an integration map.
